      <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
      <p>OSHA compliance is not optional — it is the law, and the penalties for violations are steep. But more importantly, a properly selected, inspected, and maintained fall protection system saves lives. Start with the ABCDs: anchorage, body harness, connector, and rescue plan. For the harness itself, choose ANSI Z359.11 certified equipment from reputable manufacturers like 3M or well-rated alternatives like TRSMIMA. Ensure every harness is inspected before each shift, documented annually by a competent person, and retired immediately after any fall event.</p>
      <p>Compliance is not a cost — it is the price of doing business at height.</p>

